Silvestre Name Meaning. Galician and Spanish: habitational name from any of the places named Silvestre in Pontevedra and Badajoz. Catalan, Occitan, French, and Spanish: from the personal name Silvestre (see Sylvester). Spanish and Portuguese: byname from silvestre 'wild', 'rustic'.
